Is it easier to say to this man, "Your sins are forgiven"? Or to say, "Get up, take your bed and walk"?
"I want you to know that the Son of Man has authority on earth to forgive sins." Then Jesus spoke to the man who couldn't walk.
He said, "Come on, get up. Take your things and go home."
The man stood up and took his mat. Then he walked away, while everyone watched. All the people were amazed. They praised God and said, "We have never seen anything like this!" Jesus calls Levi.
Once again Jesus went out beside the Sea of Galilee. A large crowd came to him, and he began to teach them.
